  "response": "Here are some key traffic rules and safety guidelines:\n\n1. Basic Driving Rules:\n- Always follow speed limits\n- Stop at red lights and stop signs\n- Use turn signals when changing lanes or turning\n- Yield right of way when required\n- Maintain safe following distance\n\n2. Safety Practices:\n- Wear seat belts\n- Don't drive under the influence of alcohol or drugs\n- Avoid distracted driving (using phone, eating, etc.)\n- Use headlights at night and in poor visibility\n- Check mirrors frequently\n\n3. Specific Situations:\n- Pedestrians have right of way at crosswalks\n- Slow down in school zones\n- Move over for emergency vehicles\n- Don't block intersections\n- Use proper lane for turning\n\n4. Parking Rules:\n- Don't park in handicap zones without permit\n- Obey parking signs and meters\n- Don't park in no-parking zones\n- Respect fire hydrant zones\n\n5. Additional Tips:\n- Maintain vehicle in good condition\n- Carry required documents (license, registration)\n- Follow traffic signals and road signs\n- Be courteous to other drivers\n\nRemember that specific rules can vary by country and region.",
